{
  "stem": "942.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I had nothing to eat in those 4 days, practically.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they brought this soup, and I just couldn't put it-- you know, I-- I wouldn't touch it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my father and uncle, they practically forced it down my throat, you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And you know, had they not been there, I wouldn't have, probably-- [CHUCKLES] I would have not eaten it, and I would have been a goner fast.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But, you know, they forced this soup down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And eventually, the time came when the soup tasted pretty good, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But this first experience was absolutely terrible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So this was my first day in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "After this lunch, they allowed us to walk around in camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I could see the tremendous size of this camp, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was absolutely immense.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I could see many prisoners, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I call myself a prisoner.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I really hate to say this, but I feel that I have committed a crime.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But we were called haftlings, you know?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And so, I saw many people that were going around in some pretty good-looking outfits, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And these were the people that ran the-- the infrastructure of the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They were called a prominent people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And these are mostly Polish people and criminals, German criminals, who were taken out of jails in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they ran the infrastructure.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And Polish political prisoners, they were there since 1942.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because actually, Auschwitz was built for Polish prisoners.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So those that were still alive, they got themselves into the top positions.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They were the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was called a lagteraltester, which was a prisoner, and the blockaltesters, and the [? room elders. ?] You see, every block, every barrack, had a block leader.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And each room had a room leader.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
